</li>
<li id="cite_note-preparing-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-preparing_2-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/preparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple/preparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple?lang=eng"><i>Preparing to Enter the Holy Temple</i></a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. 2019.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Preparing+to+Enter+the+Holy+Temple&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=2019&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fmanual%2Fpreparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple%2Fpreparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEndowment+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Similarity-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Similarity_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Similarity_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Similarity_3-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHomer1994" class="citation journal cs1">Homer, Michael W. (1994). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V27N03_15.pdf">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>'Similarity of priesthood in masonry': The relationship between Freemasonry and Mormonism"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>27</b> (3). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=%27Similarity+of+priesthood+in+masonry%27%3A+The+relationship+between+Freemasonry+and+Mormonism&amp;rft.volume=27&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.aulast=Homer&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael+W.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V27N03_15.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEndowment+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPrince1995" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gregory_Prince" title="Gregory Prince">Prince, Greg</a> (August 15, 1995). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220817204045/http://signaturebookslibrary.org/power-from-on-high-06/">"Ordinances: The Second Anointing"</a>. <i>Power from on High: The Development of Mormon Priesthood</i>. Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. pp.&#160;189, 191. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1560850717" title="Special:BookSources/978-1560850717"><bdi>978-1560850717</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/power-from-on-high-06/">the original</a> on August 17, 2022 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>On 10 March 1844 Smith delivered a discourse on the subject of Elijah in which he gave his most complete explanation of the second anointing. He said ... [t]he function of the ordinance was to assure salvation ... Other ordinances considered essential for exaltation were generally held to be conditional—that is, the ordinance enabled exaltation, but the subsequent righteousness of the recipient secured it. By contrast, the second anointing guaranteed one's exaltation, and thus may be viewed as the crowning ordinance of Smith's ministry.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Ordinances%3A+The+Second+Anointing&amp;rft.btitle=Power+from+on+High%3A+The+Development+of+Mormon+Priesthood&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pages=189%2C+191&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1995-08-15&amp;rft.isbn=978-1560850717&amp;rft.aulast=Prince&amp;rft.aufirst=Greg&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsignaturebookslibrary.org%2Fpower-from-on-high-06%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEndowment+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Fulness-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Fulness_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fulness_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fulness_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBuerger1983" class="citation journal cs1">Buerger, David John (1983). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V16N01_12.pdf">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>"The Fulness of the Priesthood": The Second Anointing in Latter-day Saint Theology and Practice"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>16</b> (1). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F45225125">10.2307/45225125</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/45225125">45225125</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=%22The+Fulness+of+the+Priesthood%22%3A+The+Second+Anointing+in+Latter-day+Saint+Theology+and+Practice&amp;rft.volume=16&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F45225125&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F45225125%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft.aulast=Buerger&amp;rft.aufirst=David+John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V16N01_12.pdf&am