<li id="cite_note-Sacred-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Sacred_82-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Sacred_82-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation pressrelease cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://newsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org/article/temple-worship">"First Presidency Statement on Temples"</a> (Press release). <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. January 2, 2019. <q>A dedicated temple is the most holy of any place of worship on the earth. Its ordinances are sacred and are not discussed outside a holy temple.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=First+Presidency+Statement+on+Temples&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=2019-01-02&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Farticle%2Ftemple-worship&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEndowment+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Things-83"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Things_83-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Things_83-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFChristiansen1971" class="citation magazine cs1"><a href="/wiki/ElRay_L._Christiansen" title="ElRay L. Christiansen">Christiansen, ElRay L.</a> (June 1971). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/new-era/1971/06/some-things-you-need-to-know-about-the-temple">"Some Things You Need to Know about the Temple"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/New_Era_(magazine)" title="New Era (magazine)">New Era</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. <q>The ordinances of the temple are so sacred that they are not open to the view of the public. They are available only to those who qualify through righteous living. They are performed in places dedicated especially for this purpose. Their sacred nature is such that discussion in detail outside the temple is inappropriate.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=New+Era&amp;rft.atitle=Some+Things+You+Need+to+Know+about+the+Temple&amp;rft.date=1971-06&amp;rft.aulast=Christiansen&amp;rft.aufirst=ElRay+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fnew-era%2F1971%2F06%2Fsome-things-you-need-to-know-about-the-temple&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEndowment+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
